org.gbif.occurrencestore.processor

Class FragmentProcessor

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.gbif.occurrencestore.processor.FragmentProcessor

  • public class FragmentProcessor
extends Object
    Responsible for producing and persisting Fragment objects given crawling response snippets, and sending a message reporting successful persistence. Also updates ZooKeeper with running counts of success/failure.

    • Method Detail

      • buildFragments

        public void buildFragments(UUID datasetKey,
                  byte[] data,
                  org.gbif.api.vocabulary.OccurrenceSchemaType schema,
                  org.gbif.api.vocabulary.EndpointType protocol,
                  Integer crawlId,
                  @Nullable
                  org.gbif.api.model.crawler.DwcaValidationReport validationReport)
        Takes the given response/dwca fragment and parses it into Fragment object(s) and then persists it/them. Responsible for identifying duplicates of existing Fragments and assigning ids to new Fragments. The only case where multiple Fragments are returned from this message is ABCD 2.06 snippets that are differentiated with UnitQualifiers.
        Parameters:
        datasetKey - the dataset to which this fragment belongs
        data - a snippet of xml or json from a crawler response, representing a single "record"
        schema - the crawler response type (e.g. ABCD_2_06, DWC_1_4) or DWCA for DwC-A as JSON
        protocol - the endpoint type of this occurrence's dataset (e.g. DIGIR, BIOCASE, DWC_ARCHIVE)
        crawlId - the crawl attempt that produced the snippet
        validationReport - the DwcaValidationReport if this fragment came from a DwC-A, null otherwise
